sec.p:
The scintillators were connected by adiabatic light-guides to 16-dynode photomultipliers which were oriented parallel to the magnetic field. The field of 0.4 T only reduced the response of the tubes by 30%. They had an intrinsic time resolution of 1 ns and a noise rate of less than 50 Hz. A coincidence between the two planes was required for a valid trigger. The average efficiency of the trigger counters, for single tracks, was determined with data and found to be (
97.5 ± 0.1
)%.
